    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grind most of the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> (save some for garnish!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> to form a paste</p><p>Add 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and mix well – this is your <strong>parsley oil</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don't have a pestle and mortar, chop the parsley very finely and mix with olive oil</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
